tools: github.com/nw0rn/text2speech-gptscript, playback-audio

Come up with a joke.
Turn the text into a speech. The output file should be a mp3 file named "joke". The voice is "fable".  
Pass in the name of the generated output file and playback the sound. 

--- 
name: playback-audio
description: playback the an audio file 
args: file_name: path to the file which should be played 

#!/bin/bash

#afplay is preinstalled on MacOS - Windows/Linux users need to open the file manually
if command -v "afplay" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    afplay ${file_name}  
else
    echo "Please open the ${file_name} file."
fi